This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) in social media. The paper also focuses on social connections and networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for capturing user representations, which involves machine learning techniques, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
